DTSTAMP:20260406T093857Z
DESCRIPTION:Spend the summer inside a museum\, learning from professional artists. Our workshops for children aged 8–12 are hands-on\, creative\, and fun\, covering everything from tie-dye to ceramics and more. \n\nChoose your experience\n\nRegister for individual workshops\, or go all-in with our combination ticket for access to every session throughout the camp.\n\nMay 4\n\nCeramics and Mask Making Workshop\n\nMay 5\n\nAnthotype and Cyanotype Workshop\n\nMay 6\n\nCanvas City\n\nMay 7\n\nGrowing From Nothing: A Gardening Walk Workshop\n\nMay 8\n\nNatural Tie-Dye Workshop\n\nEnd-of-camp showcase\n\nThe final day is a celebration where the participants present everything they made over the summer\, open for all families to attend.\n\nNote: \n\n-Please pack a lunch\, snacks\, and a water bottle for your child each day.\n\n-Every registered participant receives a gift store voucher of equal value\, redeemable at the MAP Gift Store. \n\n-If you're a working parent\, our café space is open for you to use while your child is in session.\n\nThese workshops are for children between the ages of 8-12. If you are between the ages of 13-16 check out our programme here.\n\nSpots are limited. Register early to secure your place.
DTEND:20260509T103000Z
DTSTART:20260504T043000Z
SUMMARY:Summer at MAP (Ages 8-12)
UID:1239@map-india.org
URL:https://map-india.org/map-events/summer-at-map-ages-8-12/
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://map-india.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Website-cover-images-new-2026-04-02T112617.763.png
CATEGORIES:Workshops,MAP,CBD
DTSTAMP:20260406T101116Z
DESCRIPTION:Five days\, a museum full of inspiration\, and a workshop unlike any other\, join film maker Hansa Thapliyal for doll-making and stop-motion animation at MAP.\n\nUsing the museum as a creative playground\, participants will work with everyday materials and scraps to build their own dolls\, drawing inspiration from our exhibition Beneath the Turning Sky. Along the way\, they'll explore their ideas\, experiment with storytelling\, and find their own creative voice.\n\nThrough playful stop-motion exercises\, these ideas will begin to move\, building into a collaborative animated film screened at the end of Summer at MAP.\n\nParticipants are required to bring:\n\n-A mobile phone with a camera\n\n-A few discarded items from home to add a personal touch to the creations\n\nNote: \n\n-Please pack a lunch\, snacks\, and a water bottle for your child each day.\n\n-Every registered participant receives a gift store voucher of equal value\, redeemable at the MAP Gift Store. \n\n-If you're a working parent\, our café space is open for you to use while your child is in session.\n\nThese workshops are for children between the ages of 13-16 If you are between the ages of 8-12 check out our programme here.\n\nSpots are limited. Register early to secure your place.
DTEND:20260509T103000Z
DTSTART:20260504T043000Z
SUMMARY:Summer at MAP (Ages 13-16)
