ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://map-india.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/Website-cover-images-new-2026-04-01T102158.137.png
CATEGORIES:Workshops,MAP,CBD
DTSTAMP:20260402T143034Z
DESCRIPTION:Krause (2013) says "a picture is worth a thousand words\, but a soundscape is worth a thousand pictures". This showcases the power of sound in both conveying information and evoking emotion.\n\nIn this workshop\, we will explore the world of sounds to understand nature-human dynamics in various spatial and temporal aspects. Hearing is different from listening\, and we engage in active listening of sound\, visualizing them using some free softwares are also part of this workshop. The landscape is changing and so is the time and climate. How our active listening and recording the sound help in understanding these changes and also start creating repositories for endangered sounds. Eg- the sound from Kabadiwala on a Sunday morning or door-to-door playing of Nadaswara in the mornings of Karthika masa could be examples of spatial and temporally embedded sound.\n\nParticipants can bring their own laptop with following softwares\nhttps://www.ravensoundsoftware.com/raven-downloads/\n\nRaven Pro ® is free for Indian Citizens\nhttps://www.audacityteam.org/download/\n\nAudacity is a light software for sound visualization\nSong meter touch (free app for both Android and iOS) by Wildlife Acoustics ®\n\nThis is part of series of events in collaboration with Srishti Manipal Institute of Art\, Design &amp\; Technology (SMI).
DTEND:20260407T130000Z
DTSTART:20260407T113000Z
SUMMARY:On Seeing the Sound in a Changing Environment
UID:1235@map-india.org
URL:https://map-india.org/map-events/on-seeing-the-sound-in-a-changing-environment/
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://map-india.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Website-cover-images-new-2026-04-07T103045.923.png
CATEGORIES:Exhibition Opening,MAP,CBD
DTSTAMP:20260407T064328Z
DESCRIPTION:Join us for the preview of warrior garments-afra eisma followed by an intimate performance by Aanchal Bordoloi and refreshments by Chef Tresa Francis from Coracle.\n\nStitched\, layered\, painted and charged with feeling\, Dutch artist afra eisma’s warrior garments  invite you into a world where anger is not contained\, but worn. afra's practice is colourful and playful\, yet quietly carries weight. Their work asks us to think about what it means to feel safe in all your vulnerabilities.\n\nAt MAP\, we believe safe spaces belong to everyone. Keeping in line with this ethos\, for the first time we are inviting all our audiences to be a part of the opening night of this exhibition. Join us afra for a guided walk of the exhibition\, followed by an intimate live performance by Aanchal Bordoloi.\n\nDrawing on years of original songwriting and the tradition of storytelling in close\, connected spaces\, Aanchal invites you into a conversation between artist and listener\, leaving you with something to carry home long after the evening ends.\n\nWe look forward to welcoming you for this special evening.
DTEND:20260410T150000Z
DTSTART:20260410T123000Z
SUMMARY:Preview Night: warrior garments
UID:1244@map-india.org
